# Cost of Scrubbing

Two different working directories for this project:
Storage on cluster: /N/project/LevScrubbing/Scrubbing-Cost (can be accessed from HPC systems)
GitHub: mandymejia/Scrubbing-paper (can be accessed from HPC systems and locally)
* GitHub repository should be cloned to 'GitHub' folder in 'Documents' on either system

To replicate:

I. On cluster with access to HCP data, run scripts numbered 1-6 in order. These scripts save results to the cluster storage project directory 
for use in later scripts.
  a. '1_ParcMatLabels.R' saves results to GitHub so it can be run locally or on IU HPC systems

II. Run "compute" scripts starting with 7 or 8.

III. Run remaining scripts starting with 7 or 8. These scripts only refer to results saved in Github and can
therefore be run locally or on HPC systems. These scripts include:
'7a_Analysis_MAE_edges.R' -- make plots related to edge-wise median absolute error analysis of FC 
'7a_Analysis_MAE_plots.R' -- make other plots related to median absolute error analysis of FC
'7b_Analysis_QCFC_plot.R' and '7b_Analysis_QCFC_dist.R' -- make plots related to QCFC and distance-QCFC analysis
'8_BWAS_visualize.R' - make plots related to brain-wise association studies values 

Note: The script 'FC_vis_funs.R' is sourced within other scripts and does not need to be run explicitly

